WEBVTT

00:01.392 --> 00:03.177
What if we partner
with a brand influencer

00:03.220 --> 00:04.656
that can help
promote Bulk Beauty?

00:04.700 --> 00:06.876
Zelda Grant has
over 10 million followers.

00:06.919 --> 00:08.399
I'd like to accept.

00:10.445 --> 00:12.447
Evan, you never responded
to my texts.

00:14.014 --> 00:15.841
I don't think it's appropriate
for there to be an us,

00:15.885 --> 00:17.452
now that we're
working together again.

00:17.495 --> 00:18.757
I'm working
and living on a farm.

00:18.801 --> 00:20.324
We call this place
The Colony.

00:20.368 --> 00:21.891
I'm Silas.

00:21.934 --> 00:23.501
JOAQUIN:
You should've heard
this guy Silas talk.

00:23.545 --> 00:25.199
He's got, like, all these women
living and working there.

00:25.242 --> 00:26.852
I think Jenna's in a cult.

00:27.114 --> 00:29.290
ASHER:
Elliot's always been
an anxious kid.

00:29.333 --> 00:31.509
I feel like
I'm screwing all this up.

00:31.553 --> 00:33.076
Laura did
most of the parenting.

00:33.120 --> 00:34.077
I had a son.

00:34.121 --> 00:35.339
His name is Jacob,

00:35.383 --> 00:36.688
and he died
when he was six years old.

00:36.732 --> 00:40.083
Dennis, I just don't have time
for casual dating.

00:40.127 --> 00:42.216
I'm not interested
in casual dating.

00:42.259 --> 00:43.782
RYAN: I want
a serious relationship,

00:43.826 --> 00:44.696
and kids.

00:45.784 --> 00:46.959
GAEL:
I want us to be a family.

00:47.003 --> 00:48.657
I wanna marry you.

00:48.700 --> 00:49.962
MR. TAVEZ: [over voice mail]
Isabella, this is your father.

00:50.006 --> 00:51.486
If I don't see proof
that you're serious

00:51.529 --> 00:52.965
about putting the baby up
for adoption,

00:53.009 --> 00:54.663
you'll leave me no choice
but to press charg--

00:54.706 --> 00:55.881
[line beeps off]

00:55.925 --> 00:56.882
Isabella Tavez,

00:56.926 --> 00:57.970
we have a warrant
for your arrest.

00:58.014 --> 01:00.147
GAEL:
Wait, wait. Whoa, whoa, whoa!

01:01.931 --> 01:04.934
["There's A Place"
by Roo Panes playing]

01:05.369 --> 01:10.940
♪ Another life, another time

01:10.983 --> 01:12.942
-DENNIS: I got you.
-[Jacob laughing]

01:12.985 --> 01:19.122
♪ Could there be a place
for you and I? ♪

01:20.080 --> 01:25.955
♪ Abandon reason
Adopt the rhyme ♪

01:26.999 --> 01:33.789
♪ And there could be a place
for us to find ♪

01:34.616 --> 01:37.184
♪ There could be a place

01:42.145 --> 01:43.929
♪ Oh, I flew home...

01:43.973 --> 01:46.932
But... you're gone.

01:49.370 --> 01:55.506
♪ I left the cape
of good hope behind ♪

01:57.073 --> 02:03.993
♪ Towards your eyes
so full of paradise ♪

02:04.689 --> 02:10.869
♪ I missed the flight
'cause you were on my mind ♪

02:11.696 --> 02:13.742
♪ Can't get you off my mind

02:20.575 --> 02:23.578
♪♪

02:45.252 --> 02:46.862
[Jacob laughing]

02:46.905 --> 02:52.433
♪ Another life, another time

02:53.608 --> 02:55.262
♪ And there could be
a place... ♪

02:55.305 --> 02:56.524
DENNIS:
I got you.

02:57.699 --> 03:00.005
♪ For us to find

03:01.006 --> 03:03.879
♪ There could be a place

03:06.055 --> 03:09.232
♪ Pa-pa-paa, pa-pa-pa-pa-pa

03:09.276 --> 03:11.016
♪ Pa-pa-paa, pa-pa-pa-pa

03:14.106 --> 03:17.327
♪ Then we'll find
our peace of mind ♪

03:18.023 --> 03:20.200
♪ You and me,
Bel Ami ♪

03:20.243 --> 03:25.640
♪ Pa-pa-pa, pa-paaa

03:43.527 --> 03:45.137
I don't know what happened.

03:45.181 --> 03:47.139
-[grunting]
-[glass shattering]

03:48.489 --> 03:49.272
I just--

03:51.318 --> 03:52.580
I snapped.

03:53.320 --> 03:54.930
I think I was so blindsided

03:54.973 --> 03:57.324
with my parents saying
we should place the baby
for adoption.

03:58.107 --> 04:00.065
And then I saw my father's car

04:00.109 --> 04:03.243
with his stupid
Car P DM vanity plate,

04:03.286 --> 04:07.203
I just-- I was so, like,
just overcome with anger.

04:07.247 --> 04:08.770
-[grunting]
-[glass shattering]

04:11.076 --> 04:12.121
And...

04:15.559 --> 04:16.995
I just wanted to, like...

04:19.346 --> 04:21.043
I wanted to hit back.

04:25.613 --> 04:27.354
Okay. I understand.

04:29.007 --> 04:31.836
But, Isabella, why
didn't you tell me about it?

04:35.057 --> 04:37.320
I was just afraid
of what you would think of me.

04:38.930 --> 04:42.020
I didn't want you to think
that I was, like,
crazy or something.

04:44.980 --> 04:49.506
Gael, I have never done
anything like this ever, okay?

04:49.550 --> 04:50.507
I swear!

04:53.380 --> 04:54.946
-Okay?
-I believe you.

04:59.647 --> 05:02.737
♪♪

05:08.960 --> 05:10.440
♪ You know, you wanna

05:10.484 --> 05:12.486
♪♪

05:12.529 --> 05:13.965
MAN:
Smile.

05:14.009 --> 05:17.186
So tell me the origins
of this all-women-owned app.

05:17.969 --> 05:21.059
Well, uh, we all met
while working at Speckulate.

05:21.103 --> 05:23.148
We called ourselves
the Fight Club Girls.

05:23.192 --> 05:24.367
I love that. Why?

05:24.411 --> 05:26.456
We were among
the few female employees

05:26.500 --> 05:28.066
at Speckulate
at the time.

05:28.110 --> 05:29.372
And it was a real boys' club--

05:29.416 --> 05:30.460
Like tech can be.

05:32.027 --> 05:34.072
And-- And we got to talking
about how great it would be

05:34.116 --> 05:35.422
to work for ourselves someday.

05:35.465 --> 05:37.119
And then we found
the courage to quit

05:37.162 --> 05:38.642
and bet on our own ideas.

05:38.686 --> 05:41.993
And I was so totally blown away
by their one-stop-app

05:42.037 --> 05:43.430
for the eco-conscious
beauty consumer,

05:43.473 --> 05:45.736
I literally begged them
to let me jump on board

05:45.780 --> 05:47.956
because I knew my fans
would love an app like this.

05:47.999 --> 05:49.871
WOMAN:
Great going, ladies.

05:51.307 --> 05:52.961
What's up, TikTok babes?

05:53.004 --> 05:54.963
I'm inviting you all
to download the Bulk Beauty app

05:55.006 --> 05:57.574
and join me using
the #sustainablebeauty
challenge!

05:57.618 --> 05:59.402
One of my favorite things
about the Bulk Beauty app

05:59.446 --> 06:00.708
is the community.

06:00.751 --> 06:02.449
The app invites you
to share product reviews

06:02.492 --> 06:03.928
with women
you're connected to.

06:03.972 --> 06:05.408
And I can access my--

06:05.452 --> 06:07.236
[all gasp, laugh]

06:07.279 --> 06:08.498
Bulk Beauty is the best,

06:08.542 --> 06:10.065
and I got this
for a discounted price.

06:10.108 --> 06:11.327
50% off if you...

06:11.371 --> 06:13.285
We've reached
250,000 subscribers!

06:14.461 --> 06:16.114
289,000!

06:18.073 --> 06:20.031
We just hit
300,000 subscribers!

06:20.075 --> 06:22.860
-What!
-[all cheering]

06:25.472 --> 06:26.298
So...

06:28.213 --> 06:29.432
what happened
at your old school?

06:30.041 --> 06:31.565
Why did you wanna stop going?

06:34.481 --> 06:35.482
The kids were mean.

06:37.614 --> 06:38.398
Mean about what?

06:45.666 --> 06:49.147
You know, I got bullied
in school when I was your age.

06:49.539 --> 06:50.932
Really? Why?

06:51.585 --> 06:53.543
Well, the kids
teased me about my weight.

06:54.109 --> 06:56.677
And... And the fact
that I didn't have a dad.

06:57.547 --> 06:58.896
I mean, I had a dad,

06:59.419 --> 07:01.029
but he left
when I was pretty young.

07:04.075 --> 07:05.033
ASHER:
Hey!

07:05.947 --> 07:07.470
Looks like
you two had fun today.

07:07.514 --> 07:09.646
-Davia makes everything fun.
-DAVIA: Ah!

07:09.690 --> 07:11.082
Hey, can she stay for dinner?

07:12.170 --> 07:13.084
I'd love to!

07:13.128 --> 07:14.521
-Yes!
-DAVIA: Yes.

07:15.260 --> 07:17.088
The sentencing hearing
has been scheduled for Friday.

07:19.134 --> 07:20.309
That-- That soon?

07:21.919 --> 07:23.704
Hey, the sooner
we get through this,
the better, right?

07:28.578 --> 07:30.101
What's the worst-case scenario?

07:30.537 --> 07:32.190
Worst case, you get jail time.

07:34.715 --> 07:36.543
Wait, how--
how much jail time?

07:36.586 --> 07:38.849
Could I-- Could I give birth
in prison?

07:39.894 --> 07:43.114
You'd probably be looking
at six to nine months.

07:43.158 --> 07:44.289
[Isabella gasps]

07:44.333 --> 07:46.117
But I spoke
with my boss, Kathleen.

07:46.161 --> 07:47.684
This is your first offense,

07:47.728 --> 07:50.208
and you're taking responsibility
for your actions,

07:50.252 --> 07:51.732
so we highly doubt

07:51.775 --> 07:53.516
you'll get anything
more than community service.

07:56.780 --> 07:58.434
Hey, whatever happens,

07:58.478 --> 08:00.436
we're gonna get through this
together, okay?

08:02.612 --> 08:03.961
Okay.

08:04.005 --> 08:07.617
Elliot is really doing great
with his schoolwork,

08:08.357 --> 08:11.316
but I feel like
he's missing out on so much

08:11.360 --> 08:12.404
by being homeschooled.

08:13.841 --> 08:16.670
Socially, academically,
not being in a classroom--

08:16.713 --> 08:18.802
Have-- Have you considered

08:18.846 --> 08:21.413
having him talk to someone
about his anxiety?

08:22.327 --> 08:24.242
Well, Laura took him
to a psychiatrist once,

08:24.286 --> 08:26.157
but they just
wanted to medicate him.

08:26.941 --> 08:29.247
Well, some kids
really benefit from medication.

08:29.291 --> 08:32.729
But there are other options
that a therapist can explore.

08:36.298 --> 08:40.041
Have you ever thought
maybe Elliot's refusal
to go to school

08:40.084 --> 08:41.869
has something to do
with his mother leaving?

08:43.261 --> 08:45.568
Elliot had these issues
long before she left.

08:45.612 --> 08:46.917
This is nothing new.

08:46.961 --> 08:50.138
What Elliot needs
is structure and consistency.

08:50.704 --> 08:51.531
We're doing fine.

08:52.793 --> 08:54.272
Even better since you came
into our lives.

08:55.883 --> 08:57.014
Well, I'm flattered,

08:58.276 --> 08:59.930
but this
is beyond my skill set.

09:00.714 --> 09:02.367
And I really think
that the goal should be

09:02.411 --> 09:03.934
getting Elliot back in school.

09:03.978 --> 09:05.457
[box clatters]

09:06.241 --> 09:07.895
I'm not going back to school.

09:07.938 --> 09:09.897
Calm down, buddy.
We were just talking--

09:09.940 --> 09:11.420
No! I-- I won't go back!

09:12.029 --> 09:13.727
Well, you have
to go back eventually.

09:13.770 --> 09:14.728
DAVIA:
Not right away,

09:14.771 --> 09:15.729
but it would be good

09:15.772 --> 09:17.165
for you
to be with other kids.

09:17.208 --> 09:19.167
No! I hate other kids.

09:19.210 --> 09:21.299
I hate everyone!
I'm not going back!

09:28.785 --> 09:31.092
We've more than doubled
our users in just a few weeks...

09:31.135 --> 09:32.397
-Wow.
-...which is insane.

09:32.441 --> 09:33.573
-Do you have any water?
-Yeah.

09:35.009 --> 09:37.315
Zelda wasn't cheap,
but she was worth every penny.

09:37.968 --> 09:39.753
Which is why we're thinking
of hiring her again

09:39.796 --> 09:41.537
for another promotion cycle.

09:41.581 --> 09:42.930
It's a lot of money,

09:43.583 --> 09:45.410
but strike while
the iron's hot, right?

09:45.454 --> 09:47.195
Hey, sounds smart to me.

09:48.413 --> 09:49.284
I'm really happy for you.

09:49.893 --> 09:50.677
Thank you.

09:52.287 --> 09:54.768
So... anything new on Silas?

09:55.812 --> 09:57.640
Yeah, something pretty big,
actually.

09:57.684 --> 09:59.250
So I finally got a copy

09:59.294 --> 10:01.731
of the license
for Silas' honey company.

10:02.514 --> 10:04.604
And now I know why
we haven't been able

10:04.647 --> 10:07.389
to find anything solid
on Silas Thompson.

10:08.303 --> 10:09.391
'Cause he's not a real person.

10:10.261 --> 10:11.219
-What?
-Yeah.

10:11.262 --> 10:14.178
Silas' real name
is Gary Brecker.

10:14.222 --> 10:16.703
I don't know why
I didn't think of him
using an alias.

10:16.746 --> 10:18.313
But feels like we've--

10:18.356 --> 10:20.271
we've just been wasting
the past few weeks

10:20.315 --> 10:22.099
going down a rabbit hole,

10:22.143 --> 10:24.406
when what I should've done
is just staked out
the farmers' market

10:24.449 --> 10:25.712
until Jenna showed up.

10:25.755 --> 10:27.714
And then, you would have
gotten arrested

10:27.757 --> 10:29.280
for violating
your restraining order.

10:29.890 --> 10:31.239
Besides, what would
you have said to her

10:31.282 --> 10:32.588
that you haven't said already?

10:33.154 --> 10:34.634
She's not gonna
leave that place

10:34.677 --> 10:37.854
unless we can prove
that Silas is a fraud.
Or Gary.

10:37.898 --> 10:39.726
And she probably
doesn't even know
that's his real name.

10:40.944 --> 10:42.685
-Yeah.
-Have you...

10:42.729 --> 10:44.818
done a social media search
on Gary Brecker?

10:44.861 --> 10:46.254
Well, I hadn't had
the chance yet

10:46.297 --> 10:48.212
when someone came by
and distracted me.

10:48.691 --> 10:50.693
Well, what are we waiting for?

10:51.476 --> 10:52.434
Let's get to work.

10:53.740 --> 10:54.871
JOAQUIN:
All right.

10:58.962 --> 11:02.574
By the way,
I know this is a casual thing,

11:02.618 --> 11:05.969
but... maybe you'd let me
take you to dinner sometime?

11:06.753 --> 11:09.494
Just as a thank you
for all your help.

11:11.366 --> 11:13.194
Sure, I'd like that.

11:16.110 --> 11:16.893
Okay.

11:17.677 --> 11:19.461
[phone vibrating]

11:19.983 --> 11:21.028
Oh, my God!

11:21.332 --> 11:22.812
What, is Harry Styles
coming to LA?

11:22.856 --> 11:24.292
No! Better!

11:24.335 --> 11:26.468
Asher, Elliot's dad,
made a therapy appointment.

11:26.511 --> 11:27.861
DENNIS:
Well, you know
you're getting old

11:27.904 --> 11:29.689
when therapy is more exciting
than a boy band.

11:29.732 --> 11:31.125
Okay, boomer.

11:31.429 --> 11:32.517
I'm not a boomer.

11:34.345 --> 11:37.305
It was a joke
because One Direction's
been on hiatus since 2015.

11:37.348 --> 11:39.089
-Wow.
-[phone vibrating]

11:39.133 --> 11:41.091
-Oh. And, uh, apparently,

11:41.135 --> 11:42.527
the therapist
would like to meet

11:42.571 --> 11:44.138
with Asher and me first.

11:44.181 --> 11:45.226
Is that weird?

11:45.269 --> 11:47.315
-I think it's weird.
-I don't.

11:47.358 --> 11:49.534
-I mean, I'm dealing
with him all day.
-And night.

11:49.578 --> 11:51.101
How many nights have you
spent at dinner over there?

11:51.145 --> 11:52.450
Interesting.

11:52.494 --> 11:54.365
How many nights
are you eating dinner with Ryan?

11:54.409 --> 11:55.932
I'm dating Ryan.

11:55.976 --> 11:57.194
Are you dating
what's-his-nuts?

11:57.238 --> 11:58.979
No! I'm his son's teacher.

11:59.588 --> 12:01.851
So, uh, what's
this Asher guy look like?

12:02.591 --> 12:05.637
Like a frat-ier version
of you, actually.

12:05.681 --> 12:06.900
Is that even possible?

12:06.943 --> 12:08.684
[Davia and Kelly laugh]

12:10.164 --> 12:11.426
I just think that
there needs to be boundaries.

12:11.469 --> 12:13.036
I mean, you're not
this guy's life coach.

12:13.080 --> 12:14.603
I know that!

12:14.646 --> 12:16.692
And neither are you! Mine!

12:16.736 --> 12:17.824
You know what I mean!

12:18.389 --> 12:19.869
I'm not trying to save anyone.

12:19.913 --> 12:21.479
I learned my lesson with you.

12:21.523 --> 12:24.091
KELLY:
Oh-ho-ho! Burn! Good one.

12:26.963 --> 12:30.488
If I didn't know any better,
which I don't...

12:30.532 --> 12:32.752
[in British accent]
...I'd say you're
a tad bit jealous.

12:41.282 --> 12:44.285
♪♪

12:52.293 --> 12:54.164
I'm really impressed
that you do this.

12:54.208 --> 12:55.252
Mm.

12:58.821 --> 13:01.215
And... the food's
actually pretty good.

13:01.258 --> 13:04.044
Oh-ho! Okay.
Solid 7 out of 10?

13:04.087 --> 13:05.697
-Uh, 7.5.
-7.5...

13:05.741 --> 13:07.787
Yeah, but the heart behind it
makes it a total 10.

13:12.400 --> 13:14.271
-I'm a fairy princess.
-Ah--

13:14.315 --> 13:16.752
GIRL:
And we have to crown her queen
before the evil fairy shows up.

13:16.796 --> 13:18.145
-Come help us!
-Oh--

13:18.188 --> 13:19.668
Uh, excuse me.

13:19.711 --> 13:22.976
Um, trouble is brewing
in Fairy Princess Land.

13:23.019 --> 13:26.457
And I'm... needed
at the princess' coronation.

13:27.371 --> 13:29.243
Understood. Good luck.

13:35.336 --> 13:36.641
I had a dream last night

13:38.295 --> 13:40.341
about, uh, Jacob.

13:40.384 --> 13:41.777
I haven't dreamt
about him in a while.

13:43.039 --> 13:44.954
He was older,
like the age he'd be now.

13:46.477 --> 13:47.957
Usually,
when I dream about him,

13:48.001 --> 13:50.307
at some point, it hits me:
he's dead.

13:50.351 --> 13:52.744
And... he vanishes.

13:54.442 --> 13:55.835
That didn't happen this time?

13:55.878 --> 13:56.966
No, I thought it would,

13:57.010 --> 13:59.273
but... he offered me his hand,

13:59.316 --> 14:00.796
I took it,

14:00.840 --> 14:03.755
and we... ran away.

14:05.627 --> 14:07.063
I wonder what that means.

14:08.456 --> 14:09.500
I don't know.

14:10.414 --> 14:11.502
Maybe it means
my days are numbered,

14:11.546 --> 14:13.069
and he's walking me
into the light.

14:13.113 --> 14:14.418
GAEL:
[laughing] Stop it.

14:17.204 --> 14:19.815
I think it might have
to do with a conversation
I had with Ryan.

14:19.859 --> 14:21.295
I might've given her
the impression

14:21.338 --> 14:23.079
that I was open
to having a baby with her,

14:23.558 --> 14:25.908
you know,
if things keep progressing.

14:26.735 --> 14:28.171
But you don't want another kid?

14:31.261 --> 14:32.306
I don't think so.

14:35.744 --> 14:37.398
You think it's a deal breaker?

14:40.183 --> 14:41.445
I think it might be.

14:44.927 --> 14:47.451
RYAN:
Tiara! [gasps] I found it!

14:47.495 --> 14:49.497
Hurry!
Before the evil fairy comes!

14:49.540 --> 14:52.500
[indistinct chatter]

14:52.543 --> 14:53.805
Thank you, both,
for being here.

14:55.633 --> 14:56.896
Davia, I'm interested
in your point of view
as Elliot's teacher,

14:56.939 --> 14:58.332
but I'd like
to start with Asher.

14:59.463 --> 15:00.334
Tell me about Elliot.

15:02.553 --> 15:03.337
Um...

15:04.555 --> 15:06.862
My son's always had
a lot of social anxiety.

15:07.515 --> 15:09.604
Uh, he didn't have
many friends,

15:09.647 --> 15:12.128
which made him
an easy target for bullies.

15:12.172 --> 15:14.565
But the panic attacks
began recently?

15:15.610 --> 15:17.394
Has anything new happened
in Elliot's life?

15:20.745 --> 15:22.399
My wife and I separated.

15:23.139 --> 15:24.184
That's significant.

15:25.750 --> 15:28.057
Does Elliot live with you
or does he go back and forth?

15:28.101 --> 15:29.929
Elliot lives with me.

15:29.972 --> 15:32.061
His mother's been
traveling in Europe.

15:33.062 --> 15:35.021
He video chats with her
about once a week,

15:36.022 --> 15:37.719
when she has reception.

15:38.589 --> 15:39.939
THERAPIST:
And when was the last time

15:39.982 --> 15:41.592
Elliot saw his mother
in person?

15:42.985 --> 15:43.768
Um...

15:46.249 --> 15:48.164
The day that she told us
she was leaving.

15:49.383 --> 15:51.298
She told
you and Elliot together?

15:51.341 --> 15:52.908
Yeah, she sat us down

15:52.952 --> 15:55.128
and told us
that she wasn't happy

15:56.477 --> 15:58.087
and that she needed
to leave for a while.

15:59.523 --> 16:01.612
THERAPIST:
That must've been
very painful for you.

16:03.440 --> 16:05.355
We-- We're not here
to talk about me.

16:10.143 --> 16:11.796
THERAPIST:
Had Elliot ever refused
to go to school

16:11.840 --> 16:13.102
before his mother left?

16:13.624 --> 16:16.801
Yes, but Laura
always got him there.

16:16.845 --> 16:19.848
Like I said, my son's
always had social anxiety.

16:19.891 --> 16:21.067
He's never liked school.

16:21.110 --> 16:23.286
So what we need to focus on

16:23.330 --> 16:25.897
is how to get him back
into a real classroom.

16:28.465 --> 16:29.423
Eventually.

16:29.466 --> 16:31.077
There's no hurry.

16:32.078 --> 16:34.994
Cognitive behavioral therapy
can be very effective

16:35.037 --> 16:36.256
for children with anxiety.

16:36.299 --> 16:37.866
And there are tools

16:37.909 --> 16:40.347
that can be implemented at home
and during Davia's lessons

16:40.390 --> 16:42.479
to help him cope with triggers.

16:42.523 --> 16:43.872
O-- Okay. Great!

16:44.655 --> 16:45.569
What are those?

16:48.181 --> 16:51.314
♪♪

16:53.490 --> 16:57.146
[indistinct chatter]

17:00.193 --> 17:01.063
Hi, there.

17:03.283 --> 17:04.980
My space car.

17:05.024 --> 17:06.112
I see that. That's right.

17:06.155 --> 17:07.417
And you're
a really good driver.

17:08.288 --> 17:10.159
-Pilot.
-Oh, right.

17:10.203 --> 17:12.205
Of course, pilot. Yep.

17:12.944 --> 17:17.210
-Zoom. Zoom. Rrr...
-Oh! So fast! Yeah.

17:20.387 --> 17:21.170
Well...

17:22.954 --> 17:26.175
["Wild World"
by Saint Elsinore playing]

17:29.222 --> 17:34.923
♪ From an open sky we fell

17:34.966 --> 17:39.841
♪ Down the deepest
wishing well ♪

17:39.884 --> 17:46.195
♪ Your eyes saw
a whole wild world ♪

17:46.239 --> 17:49.242
Okay. Do you wanna
go over to the trains?

17:52.332 --> 17:57.772
♪ Where the light
is soft and gray ♪

17:57.815 --> 18:03.125
♪ Won't you take me there
one day? ♪

18:03.169 --> 18:09.175
♪ Out in the whole wild world

18:10.959 --> 18:17.966
♪ Have you heard
it's a wild world ♪

18:19.010 --> 18:20.142
♪♪

18:40.815 --> 18:41.642
You're here late.

18:43.209 --> 18:44.514
You are too.

18:44.558 --> 18:47.343
Well, my app isn't going
as well as Bulk Beauty's.

18:47.387 --> 18:50.085
Hiring Zelda
was the right move.

18:51.217 --> 18:52.653
Definitely was. Agreed.

18:55.264 --> 18:57.179
Oh, uh,
the elevator's not working.

18:57.223 --> 18:58.354
We have to take the stairs.

18:59.355 --> 19:01.270
Oh, good.
I need to get my steps in.

19:02.228 --> 19:04.360
♪♪

19:04.969 --> 19:05.753
After you.

19:10.105 --> 19:11.672
Since things
are going so well,

19:11.715 --> 19:13.108
we should be able
to give you

19:13.152 --> 19:14.892
our first quarterly payment
this week

19:14.936 --> 19:17.156
and, hopefully, buy you out
by the end of next year.

19:18.287 --> 19:19.549
That's great. Sounds good.

19:25.381 --> 19:26.165
It's locked.

19:28.384 --> 19:29.994
-It's locked!
-It's locked.

19:30.430 --> 19:32.301
-It's locked.
-Locked.

19:36.131 --> 19:36.914
Locked.

19:38.307 --> 19:39.482
Are we the last ones
in the building?

19:39.526 --> 19:40.701
What if--

19:41.354 --> 19:42.485
What if we're trapped
in here all night?

19:42.529 --> 19:44.705
Okay, don't panic.
We'll just call someone.

19:46.489 --> 19:47.925
-Do you have service?
-No.

19:50.276 --> 19:51.712
What if no one finds us
until the morning?

19:53.409 --> 19:54.410
[loudly] Hello!

19:54.454 --> 19:56.195
[loudly]
Hello, can you hear us?

19:56.238 --> 19:57.413
Is anyone out there?

19:57.457 --> 20:00.416
-Help!
-We're banging on the door!

20:00.460 --> 20:02.113
Hello! Can you hear us?

20:04.594 --> 20:06.553
Ugh, I can't believe this.

20:08.859 --> 20:09.773
Are you hungry?

20:11.122 --> 20:12.602
Are you trying to torture me?

20:13.124 --> 20:14.778
Why would I be trying
to torture you?

20:14.822 --> 20:16.824
It-- It was a joke.

20:16.867 --> 20:18.260
Because there's
no food in here.

20:19.000 --> 20:20.610
Oh, I have a protein bar.

20:21.568 --> 20:22.438
We can split it.

20:23.047 --> 20:24.310
Oh, okay.

20:34.276 --> 20:35.756
No, I can't--

20:35.799 --> 20:37.540
I can't be trapped
in here anymore.

20:38.019 --> 20:41.370
[loudly]
Hello? Can anyone hear me?

20:41.414 --> 20:42.589
Try to breathe.

20:42.632 --> 20:44.417
Don't think about it
like being trapped.

20:44.460 --> 20:46.332
And, you know,
at least we're together.

20:48.290 --> 20:51.815
[screaming loudly]
Is anyone there? Help! Hello!

20:52.729 --> 20:55.297
Wow. Thanks a lot.

20:56.820 --> 20:57.604
What?

20:58.692 --> 21:00.041
I said,
"At least we're together,"

21:00.084 --> 21:01.651
and you started pounding
on the door again.

21:02.043 --> 21:03.871
Do you really hate
being around me that much?

21:05.438 --> 21:06.482
Of course not.

21:07.657 --> 21:08.832
Well, you could've fooled me.

21:09.746 --> 21:11.705
You've been so cold
and shut down around me,

21:11.748 --> 21:12.662
and I don't know why.

21:13.881 --> 21:15.230
You didn't even stay
at the launch party

21:15.274 --> 21:16.405
when you said that you would.

21:18.842 --> 21:20.670
I get that you were hurt
when we broke up,

21:20.714 --> 21:23.325
but at the time,
I had no choice.

21:23.369 --> 21:26.894
And when I tried to reach out
so we could talk about us,

21:26.937 --> 21:28.548
-you totally blew me off.
-I--

21:31.290 --> 21:32.856
I didn't blow you off.

21:37.774 --> 21:39.689
I came to The Coterie
to talk in person,

21:41.212 --> 21:42.866
but you were kissing somebody
in your loft.

21:43.737 --> 21:44.520
So I left.

21:47.567 --> 21:48.959
You saw me with Joaquin.

21:49.482 --> 21:50.613
I don't know his name.

21:51.962 --> 21:53.312
The back of his head
is very distinctive

21:53.355 --> 21:56.967
with hipster neck tattoos
and... whatnot.

21:58.229 --> 21:59.361
That was the same
back of the head

21:59.405 --> 22:00.884
that I saw talking to you

22:01.885 --> 22:02.973
at the launch party.

22:04.801 --> 22:08.718
And touching your... elbow
in a flirtatious manner.

22:10.938 --> 22:12.635
So that's why
you're upset with me?

22:14.985 --> 22:18.032
Because you thought you saw me
kissing some other guy.

22:19.816 --> 22:20.643
Well, I wasn't.

22:22.602 --> 22:23.646
Joaquin kissed me.

22:28.651 --> 22:30.044
So, uh...

22:32.829 --> 22:33.874
What does that mean?

22:34.614 --> 22:37.921
♪♪

22:47.496 --> 22:50.499
♪♪

22:59.203 --> 23:00.074
Hey.

23:01.467 --> 23:03.033
What are you doing out here?

23:03.077 --> 23:04.992
I'm just taking in the mountains

23:05.514 --> 23:06.863
in your beautiful backyard.

23:06.907 --> 23:08.212
[Asher laughs]

23:08.256 --> 23:09.866
I've never lived anywhere
with a backyard before.

23:11.215 --> 23:14.001
Laura found this house
and decorated it.

23:14.044 --> 23:15.481
-As you can tell.
-[Davia chuckles]

23:16.220 --> 23:18.875
I wasn't much of a suburbs guy,
but I got used to it.

23:19.572 --> 23:20.921
Well, I can see why.

23:21.748 --> 23:24.533
Wide streets,
ample parking, quiet.

23:24.577 --> 23:28.189
I mean, I love living downtown,
but... this is tempting.

23:30.626 --> 23:33.673
Thank you for going
to therapy with me yesterday.

23:34.848 --> 23:38.591
I think this CBT is going
to be great for Elliot.

23:38.634 --> 23:41.289
And she said
it might be only
about ten sessions.

23:42.290 --> 23:43.944
I think it's gonna
be really helpful for Elliot

23:43.987 --> 23:45.728
-to have someone to talk to.
-Hmm.

23:48.514 --> 23:49.384
And what about you?

23:50.559 --> 23:52.605
Ever thought about
talking to someone?

23:53.562 --> 23:54.520
About what?

23:55.129 --> 23:56.173
About your wife leaving.

23:59.089 --> 24:00.743
Hey. What are you guys doing?

24:01.614 --> 24:02.528
We were just talking.

24:04.225 --> 24:05.008
About your mom.

24:07.620 --> 24:08.882
It's fine, Elliot.

24:08.925 --> 24:10.057
Why do you always say that?

24:10.927 --> 24:12.407
Aren't you sad Mom left?

24:13.190 --> 24:14.496
Of course, I'm sad.

24:14.540 --> 24:15.802
ELLIOT:
You don't seem like it.

24:16.150 --> 24:17.586
You act like nothing happened.

24:19.545 --> 24:20.894
Did Mom leave because of me?

24:21.982 --> 24:24.637
Hey, wh-- why would you
think that?

24:25.072 --> 24:25.899
Because I'm bad?

24:28.597 --> 24:30.207
Why would you think
you're bad?

24:31.252 --> 24:32.993
Because I don't have
any friends,

24:33.036 --> 24:34.429
I don't like school,

24:34.951 --> 24:36.387
I get upset at things.

24:36.823 --> 24:39.565
Maybe Mom just got tired
of having to take care of me.

24:41.349 --> 24:42.829
Isn't that why
you want to leave?

24:44.004 --> 24:45.614
I-- I don't wanna leave,
Elliot.

24:45.658 --> 24:48.791
ASHER:
Okay. Hey. Hey. Hey.
Let's go inside.

24:48.835 --> 24:50.489
Okay, come on,
let's sit down.

24:56.451 --> 24:59.454
[indistinct chatter]

25:12.859 --> 25:17.037
♪♪

25:29.223 --> 25:30.529
JUDGE:
Is everyone ready?

25:31.617 --> 25:32.400
Yes, Your Honor.

25:32.748 --> 25:33.967
Yes, we are, Your Honor.

25:37.405 --> 25:38.188
Elliot...

25:39.799 --> 25:42.105
your mom left

25:42.149 --> 25:43.977
because she wasn't happy
with me.

25:45.152 --> 25:48.024
Then why did she tell us both
that she wasn't happy?

25:50.287 --> 25:54.117
I think maybe your mom
was unhappy with herself,

25:54.814 --> 25:55.597
inside.

25:56.990 --> 26:00.646
And that has nothing
to do with you or your dad.

26:01.864 --> 26:06.129
Sometimes people try
to fix their unhappiness

26:06.173 --> 26:07.174
by running away,

26:08.218 --> 26:09.655
even from the people they love.

26:10.960 --> 26:13.876
ASHER:
And, Elliot, I am sad
that your mom is gone.

26:15.225 --> 26:18.141
And I thought that
by holding my sadness in,

26:18.620 --> 26:21.144
I was being strong for you.

26:22.406 --> 26:24.844
But maybe I was just trying

26:24.887 --> 26:27.281
to avoid feeling
the bad feelings

26:27.324 --> 26:28.499
because it hurts.

26:31.546 --> 26:32.547
It's okay, Dad.

26:34.201 --> 26:35.202
You have me.

26:40.686 --> 26:42.252
Elliot, I promise you,

26:43.819 --> 26:45.691
I am never going to leave you.

26:47.388 --> 26:48.171
Ever.

26:53.307 --> 26:55.962
♪♪

27:02.272 --> 27:03.622
Good morning.

27:03.665 --> 27:04.623
CLAIRE:
Hi, how late did
you stay last night?

27:05.319 --> 27:07.538
-Just a little after midnight.
-Oof!

27:07.582 --> 27:10.803
Well, with greater success
comes greater work.

27:11.630 --> 27:13.370
I was up so late,
I can't even see straight.

27:15.285 --> 27:16.722
Hey!

27:16.765 --> 27:19.202
I'm so psyched
y'all wanna do another campaign.

27:19.246 --> 27:21.640
We're so happy to have you
as our brand influencer.

27:21.683 --> 27:23.076
Yeah, and part of the team!

27:23.119 --> 27:24.381
Me too!

27:24.425 --> 27:26.122
And we've just been
approached by Pertutti,

27:26.166 --> 27:28.559
which is this huge,
intentionally inclusive brand.

27:29.343 --> 27:31.954
Pertutti means "for all"
in Italian.

27:31.998 --> 27:33.173
They want us to promote

27:33.216 --> 27:34.696
their line of
menstrual hygiene products

27:34.740 --> 27:36.306
on our app,
with their tagline:

27:36.350 --> 27:38.047
"For people
who have periods."

27:39.701 --> 27:41.181
Wait, why "people"
and not just "women"?

27:41.224 --> 27:42.878
I mean,
only women get periods.

27:43.400 --> 27:46.490
Well, trans men
and non-binary people
can also get periods.

27:46.534 --> 27:47.970
[scoffs] Whatever.

27:48.014 --> 27:50.233
I've got some really fun ideas
for the next campaign,

27:50.277 --> 27:52.235
but I've got to run for now.

27:52.279 --> 27:53.323
Let's get a meeting
on the books.

27:57.893 --> 28:00.200
What was that?

28:00.243 --> 28:02.506
Did she just... scoff?

28:02.550 --> 28:04.421
-Yeah, she definitely scoffed.
-Yeah.

28:05.379 --> 28:07.250
MARIANA:
Unfortunately,
some women believe

28:07.294 --> 28:08.774
that trans
and non-binary people

28:08.817 --> 28:10.253
should be excluded
from things

28:10.297 --> 28:12.299
that they consider
to be only for women.

28:12.908 --> 28:16.346
Uh, but we want all people
to feel welcomed by Bulk Beauty,

28:16.390 --> 28:18.087
regardless
of how they identify.

28:18.261 --> 28:20.960
We don't want someone
with beliefs like that
representing us,

28:21.961 --> 28:22.962
do we?

28:25.965 --> 28:27.488
Well, maybe she misunderstood
what we said.

28:27.531 --> 28:29.969
Or we misunderstood
what she said.

28:32.841 --> 28:35.104
We just asked her
to do another campaign.

28:39.021 --> 28:41.023
[phone vibrating]

28:48.857 --> 28:52.208
-[Isabella grunting]
-[glass breaking]

28:57.779 --> 28:59.346
[glass breaking sounds
continue over video]

29:10.487 --> 29:12.185
Will the defendant
please stand?

29:18.191 --> 29:21.107
It is my understanding
the State has offered a plea

29:21.150 --> 29:22.630
by which the felony charge

29:22.673 --> 29:24.371
will be reduced
to a misdemeanor.

29:24.414 --> 29:26.068
Is that correct, counselors?

29:26.112 --> 29:27.113
-Yes, Your Honor.
-Yes, Your Honor.

29:27.156 --> 29:28.462
JUDGE:
And, Ms. Tavez,

29:28.505 --> 29:30.769
do you understand
that if I accept your plea,

29:30.812 --> 29:32.335
you will be convicted
of the crime

29:32.379 --> 29:34.076
to which you are
pleading guilty today

29:34.120 --> 29:35.208
and you will
not have a trial?

29:37.123 --> 29:38.124
Yes, I understand.

29:39.038 --> 29:39.821
And, uh--

29:41.518 --> 29:42.737
I just want to say

29:42.781 --> 29:44.826
how sorry I am
for my actions, Your Honor.

29:44.870 --> 29:47.046
I think that apology
belongs to your parents.

29:48.090 --> 29:49.962
I'm disturbed
by what you did to their car.

29:50.571 --> 29:52.878
And, frankly, worried
about your impulse control

29:52.921 --> 29:54.967
in spite of this
being your first offense.

29:58.709 --> 30:00.276
But the court accepts
defendant's plea

30:00.320 --> 30:01.887
and sentences Ms. Tavez

30:01.930 --> 30:04.063
to 50 hours
of community service

30:04.541 --> 30:06.935
and 18 months
of summary probation.

30:06.979 --> 30:08.502
I'll hear the next case.

30:09.372 --> 30:12.114
Your Honor,
we're Isabella's parents.

30:13.202 --> 30:14.073
May we address the court?

30:14.116 --> 30:15.161
Quickly.

30:16.423 --> 30:17.946
My wife and I would like
the court to intervene

30:17.990 --> 30:20.079
for the safety
of our daughter's child.

30:21.471 --> 30:24.518
Isabella has a history
of erratic, dangerous behavior

30:24.561 --> 30:25.998
and anger management issues.

30:26.041 --> 30:26.999
ROWAN:
Objection.

30:27.042 --> 30:29.044
She was expelled
from high school,

30:29.088 --> 30:31.742
has been caught shoplifting
multiple times,

30:31.786 --> 30:34.093
and she burned
our wedding album once

30:34.136 --> 30:35.311
in a fit of rage.

30:35.355 --> 30:36.878
MR. TAVEZ:
Nearly burned our house down.

30:36.922 --> 30:38.140
ROWAN:
Objection!

30:38.184 --> 30:40.012
This is improper, Your Honor.
My client--

30:40.055 --> 30:41.317
MR. TAVEZ:
We love our daughter,

30:43.537 --> 30:45.147
but she's not fit
to be a mother.

30:45.974 --> 30:48.803
JUDGE:
Mr. and Mrs. Tavez,
I appreciate your concern,

30:48.847 --> 30:50.849
but this isn't going
to be heard in my courtroom.

30:51.632 --> 30:53.373
Any concerns
for the baby's safety

30:53.416 --> 30:55.331
should be addressed
in family court.

30:55.375 --> 30:56.463
There, you can request

30:56.506 --> 30:58.160
Child Protective Services'
oversight

30:58.204 --> 30:59.814
once the baby is born.

31:00.075 --> 31:01.076
Next case, please.

31:07.561 --> 31:08.954
["Good"
by Sleeping Lion playing]

31:08.997 --> 31:11.478
♪ I got a problem
with options ♪

31:11.521 --> 31:15.830
♪ It was easier when you were
the only one calling ♪

31:15.874 --> 31:18.441
♪ Now I'm tryna be honest

31:18.485 --> 31:20.443
♪ But I'm buying time
with little lies ♪

31:20.487 --> 31:22.271
♪ And you can tell
I'm stalling ♪

31:22.315 --> 31:26.275
♪ And there's no way...

31:26.667 --> 31:28.451
What's the story
with that piece?

31:29.539 --> 31:32.499
♪ But I can't stay

31:32.542 --> 31:36.155
♪ By, now, I thought
it'd be different... ♪

31:37.199 --> 31:39.506
I used to have
a large photo of my son there.

31:43.684 --> 31:46.252
Put it up when I was
in a particularly dark place.

31:46.992 --> 31:48.558
Trying to hold
his memory close.

31:50.473 --> 31:52.432
Then I realized it was keeping
the pain close too.

31:54.564 --> 31:55.870
But I couldn't imagine
bringing it down,

31:55.914 --> 31:59.918
so I asked Gael
to... do something over it.

32:02.355 --> 32:04.052
Something beautiful
that I could look at,

32:04.096 --> 32:06.359
and... had Jacob inside it.

32:09.014 --> 32:10.841
I can't imagine
what it would be like

32:10.885 --> 32:11.973
to lose a child.

32:20.068 --> 32:21.417
I'm so sorry.

32:23.376 --> 32:25.987
♪ And it's hard
to fight against them ♪

32:26.031 --> 32:27.554
♪ Oh, I don't say no

32:27.597 --> 32:29.904
♪ Even though I know
I should probably leave... ♪

32:30.557 --> 32:31.775
When you asked me
what we were doing,

32:31.819 --> 32:33.081
and you said you wanted
to have kids soon,

32:33.125 --> 32:34.691
I may have given you
the impression

32:34.735 --> 32:36.650
that I was open to that.

32:38.695 --> 32:40.045
Is that something...

32:41.829 --> 32:42.961
you're not open to?

32:44.223 --> 32:45.528
I didn't think I was.

32:49.402 --> 32:50.577
Until we were at the hospital

32:50.620 --> 32:52.971
and that little boy
jumped up on my lap

32:54.320 --> 32:55.234
with his little car.

32:56.496 --> 32:57.627
Took my hand.

33:00.717 --> 33:02.371
Reminded me of a dream
I had about Jacob,

33:02.415 --> 33:03.677
where he took my hand.

33:06.245 --> 33:07.942
Still don't really know
what it means, but...

33:09.596 --> 33:10.684
Well...

33:11.859 --> 33:13.556
Maybe he's giving me
permission, uh...

33:18.648 --> 33:19.998
To be happy?

33:23.523 --> 33:26.178
To give all the love you have
to another beautiful soul.

33:31.487 --> 33:32.532
Maybe.

33:34.229 --> 33:37.232
♪♪

33:43.108 --> 33:44.457
I know there are no guarantees.

33:46.111 --> 33:46.937
I just--

33:50.376 --> 33:53.161
I wanted to know
that you're...

33:54.858 --> 33:56.469
open to all possibilities...

33:58.340 --> 33:59.559
and that there's nothing...

34:01.300 --> 34:03.171
and no one else
holding you back.

34:08.089 --> 34:10.048
I am open to all possibilities,

34:11.397 --> 34:13.138
even having
another child someday.

34:19.361 --> 34:22.364
♪♪

34:26.847 --> 34:28.153
[Gael exhales]

34:28.196 --> 34:30.068
You've hardly said anything
to me since court.

34:32.331 --> 34:34.159
I'm just
processing everything.

34:36.030 --> 34:38.163
Some of what
my parents said was true,

34:39.294 --> 34:41.427
but I was a teenager
at that time.

34:41.470 --> 34:43.864
I-- I'm a different person now.
I've changed.

34:45.213 --> 34:47.128
Isabella, you smashed
your parents' car

34:47.172 --> 34:48.260
just last month.

34:50.958 --> 34:52.699
I was trying
to protect our baby.

34:55.702 --> 34:58.183
How is lashing out
and risking your freedom,

34:58.226 --> 34:59.314
protecting the baby?

34:59.358 --> 35:00.881
You could've gone
to jail, Isabella!

35:00.924 --> 35:03.579
See, I-- I-- I knew
that you were gonna do that.

35:03.623 --> 35:05.581
That-- That's exactly
why I didn't tell you.

35:05.625 --> 35:07.105
'Cause I knew that
you were going to judge me!

35:07.148 --> 35:08.715
I'm not judging you.
I'm just trying to understand.

35:08.758 --> 35:11.109
-Can you please just sit down?
-What does this mean?

35:12.240 --> 35:14.677
Are-- Are you gonna leave me?
Have your feelings changed?

35:14.721 --> 35:17.550
No! But I think we should talk
about what happened!

35:17.593 --> 35:20.901
You said that you wanted
to marry me after the wedding.

35:20.944 --> 35:22.250
That was weeks ago,

35:22.294 --> 35:24.165
and you haven't said
anything about it since.

35:24.209 --> 35:25.210
Why is that?

35:26.559 --> 35:28.213
Because we've had
bigger things to deal with.

35:30.171 --> 35:31.259
You're lying.

35:32.826 --> 35:34.306
-You're lying to me.
-Isabella, please.

35:34.349 --> 35:37.222
No, because you--
you never loved me.

35:37.265 --> 35:40.050
You-- You never chose me.

35:40.094 --> 35:41.922
You just-- You just
wanted to be with me

35:41.965 --> 35:43.880
because I'm having the baby!

35:43.924 --> 35:45.926
-Isabella!
-You never loved me!

35:45.969 --> 35:47.580
-And you never
wanted to marry me!
-Isabella, stop. Stop!

35:47.623 --> 35:48.711
[grunts] Shit!

35:49.234 --> 35:52.193
♪♪

35:55.153 --> 35:56.328
Oh, my God! Oh, my God.

35:56.371 --> 35:57.720
Gael, I-- I didn't mean
to hit you.

35:57.764 --> 35:59.331
-Don't. Don't. Don't touch me.
-I didn't mean--

35:59.374 --> 36:00.549
Just get away from me!

36:00.593 --> 36:01.594
[gasps]

36:08.035 --> 36:09.732
Thank you. Again.

36:11.081 --> 36:13.693
You've done so much for us
in such a short time.

36:14.955 --> 36:16.652
Well, I'm happy to help.

36:18.741 --> 36:22.223
Something you said to me
really made a lot of sense.

36:22.267 --> 36:24.269
Laura was never really happy.

36:25.139 --> 36:26.271
And I think she thought

36:26.314 --> 36:27.924
that getting married
and having Elliot

36:27.968 --> 36:28.838
would change that.

36:28.882 --> 36:30.318
And then when it didn't, she--

36:33.147 --> 36:35.018
Anyway, the point is,

36:35.062 --> 36:37.412
I think I should find
someone to talk to.

36:39.240 --> 36:41.199
I don't expect you
to be our therapist.

36:44.332 --> 36:45.768
I'm happy to hear that

36:45.812 --> 36:48.075
because I am no longer
in the saving-people business.

36:48.858 --> 36:49.642
[Davia clears throat]

36:53.298 --> 36:55.256
-I'll see you on Monday.
-See you.

36:56.170 --> 36:56.953
Good night.

37:00.392 --> 37:04.744
♪ Lay your troubles down
beside my door ♪

37:06.441 --> 37:10.576
♪ Come and rest with me...

37:11.359 --> 37:12.404
[knock on door]

37:13.448 --> 37:15.276
Hey. You ready for dinner?

37:16.582 --> 37:19.237
Actually, I had a rough day.

37:19.759 --> 37:20.977
And I was wondering

37:21.021 --> 37:22.327
if we could do dinner
another time?

37:23.589 --> 37:24.981
I'm sorry, I just--

37:25.025 --> 37:27.070
I-- I don't think I would be
good company tonight.

37:27.419 --> 37:29.334
Yeah, no. Sure.
It's no problem.

37:30.639 --> 37:31.423
Thanks for understanding.

37:31.988 --> 37:35.470
♪ Oh, let it be

37:40.345 --> 37:43.304
♪♪

37:49.136 --> 37:50.833
So that's why
you're upset with me?

37:53.009 --> 37:56.186
Because you thought you saw me
kissing some other guy?

37:57.927 --> 37:58.798
Well, I wasn't.

38:00.713 --> 38:01.888
Joaquin kissed me.

38:06.893 --> 38:08.242
So, uh...

38:11.027 --> 38:12.377
What does that mean?

38:18.383 --> 38:21.342
♪♪

38:30.308 --> 38:31.091
Excuse me.

38:32.310 --> 38:33.223
-EVAN: No, no, no, no!
-Wait, let us out!

38:38.968 --> 38:40.056
So...

38:41.971 --> 38:46.541
he was kissing you,
but you weren't kissing him?

38:47.412 --> 38:48.238
Right.

38:49.370 --> 38:51.416
Nothing was going on
between us.

38:57.465 --> 38:58.510
Then.

39:01.469 --> 39:02.296
Then?

39:03.993 --> 39:05.560
Nothing was going on then.

39:06.431 --> 39:10.913
And I did want to talk
to you that night about us.

39:10.957 --> 39:14.787
But... after
you were so cold to me

39:14.830 --> 39:18.094
and you insisted on keeping
everything professional,

39:19.531 --> 39:22.795
I did sort of
get involved with Joaquin.

39:26.015 --> 39:26.799
I see.

39:31.412 --> 39:33.545
Well, I guess there's
nothing more to say.
Good night then.

39:36.286 --> 39:40.595
♪ We were balancing
a fine line ♪

39:40.639 --> 39:45.034
♪ Always putting up
a good fight ♪

39:45.078 --> 39:51.389
♪ Now we know it's time
to meet the moment ♪

39:53.869 --> 39:58.047
♪ Know we've come so far
from long past ♪

39:58.091 --> 40:02.530
♪ But can we carry on,
don't look back? ♪

40:02.574 --> 40:08.928
♪ One day, if we rise
to the moment ♪

40:10.190 --> 40:14.542
♪ Know we've got
the strength to hold on ♪

40:14.586 --> 40:18.938
♪ But can we take the heat
when the road's long? ♪

40:18.981 --> 40:25.161
♪ One day, if we meet
at the distance ♪

40:27.512 --> 40:31.864
♪ How much can we take
before we break down? ♪

40:36.912 --> 40:38.174
I'm sorry to wake you up.

40:38.827 --> 40:39.611
It's okay.

40:41.526 --> 40:42.352
What's going on?

40:44.442 --> 40:45.791
I'm really freaking out, man.

40:50.360 --> 40:54.582
♪ How much can we take
before we break down? ♪
